---
import ChapterLayout from '../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro';
---

<ChapterLayout 
  title="From Curiosity to Code - Chapter II" 
  description="Follow Kaustubh's path from computer repair curiosity to software engineering expertise"
  chapter="Chapter II" 
  chapterTitle="From Curiosity to Code" 
  chapterColor="sky"
>
  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-8">
        Every developer has a spark
      </h2>
      <div class="prose text-ink-700 text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        <p>
          Every developer has a spark — a moment when curiosity meets creation. Mine began with a single question:
        </p>
        <blockquote class="text-2xl font-heading text-sky-600 italic border-l-4 border-sky-300 pl-6 my-8">
          "How do computers actually work?"
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          That question sent me down a rabbit hole I'm still happily exploring today.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Timeline -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 to-mint-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-16 text-center">
        Timeline of My Journey
      </h2>
      
      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Timeline Line -->
        <div class="absolute left-1/2 transform -translate-x-1/2 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-sky-300 to-mint-300 h-full hidden lg:block"></div>
        
        <div class="space-y-12">
          <!-- 2019 - The Spark -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="lg:text-right">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-r-4 border-sky-400">
                <div class="flex items-center lg:justify-end mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-400 to-sky-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4 lg:mr-0 lg:ml-4 lg:order-2">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M12,8A4,4 0 0,1 16,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,16A4,4 0 0,1 8,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,8M12,10A2,2 0 0,0 10,12A2,2 0 0,0 12,14A2,2 0 0,0 14,12A2,2 0 0,0 12,10M10,22C9.75,22 9.54,21.82 9.5,21.58L9.13,18.93C8.5,18.68 7.96,18.34 7.44,17.94L4.95,18.95C4.73,19.03 4.46,18.95 4.34,18.73L2.34,15.27C2.21,15.05 2.27,14.78 2.46,14.63L4.57,12.97L4.5,12L4.57,11L2.46,9.37C2.27,9.22 2.21,8.95 2.34,8.73L4.34,5.27C4.46,5.05 4.73,4.96 4.95,5.05L7.44,6.05C7.96,5.66 8.5,5.32 9.13,5.07L9.5,2.42C9.54,2.18 9.75,2 10,2H14C14.25,2 14.46,2.18 14.5,2.42L14.87,5.07C15.5,5.32 16.04,5.66 16.56,6.05L19.05,5.05C19.27,4.96 19.54,5.05 19.66,5.27L21.66,8.73C21.79,8.95 21.73,9.22 21.54,9.37L19.43,11L19.5,12L19.43,13L21.54,14.63C21.73,14.78 21.79,15.05 21.66,15.27L19.66,18.73C19.54,18.95 19.27,19.04 19.05,18.95L16.56,17.95C16.04,18.34 15.5,18.68 14.87,18.93L14.5,21.58C14.46,21.82 14.25,22 14,22H10M11.25,4L10.88,6.61C9.68,6.86 8.62,7.5 7.85,8.39L5.44,7.35L4.69,8.65L6.8,10.2C6.4,11.37 6.4,12.64 6.8,13.8L4.68,15.36L5.43,16.66L7.86,15.62C8.63,16.5 9.68,17.14 10.87,17.38L11.24,20H12.76L13.13,17.39C14.32,17.14 15.37,16.5 16.14,15.62L18.57,16.66L19.32,15.36L17.2,13.81C17.6,12.64 17.6,11.37 17.2,10.2L19.31,8.65L18.56,7.35L16.15,8.39C15.38,7.5 14.32,6.86 13.12,6.62L12.75,4H11.25Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-sky-600 lg:order-1">2019</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">The Spark</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  It all started with a glitchy desktop and way too much curiosity. I ended up repairing it myself, which led to hours spent watching how-to videos and reading about computer systems. That's when I realized: <strong>tech is magic — logical, elegant, and limitless.</strong>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- 2020 - Hello World -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
            <div class="lg:text-left">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-mint-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-l-4 border-mint-400">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-mint-400 to-mint-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M8,3A2,2 0 0,0 6,5V9A2,2 0 0,1 4,11H3V13H4A2,2 0 0,1 6,15V19A2,2 0 0,0 8,21H10V19H8V14A2,2 0 0,0 6,12A2,2 0 0,0 8,10V5H10V3M16,3A2,2 0 0,1 18,5V9A2,2 0 0,0 20,11H21V13H20A2,2 0 0,0 18,15V19A2,2 0 0,1 16,21H14V19H16V14A2,2 0 0,1 18,12A2,2 0 0,1 16,10V5H14V3H16Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-mint-600">2020</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">Hello, World!</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  My first official line of code was <code class="bg-mint-100 text-mint-700 px-2 py-1 rounded">print("Hello, World!")</code> in Python. It was a small moment, but it sparked something big. I loved how a few words on a screen could turn into something real, creative, and interactive.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- 2021 - The Deep Dive -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="lg:text-right">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-blush-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-r-4 border-blush-400">
                <div class="flex items-center lg:justify-end mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-blush-400 to-blush-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4 lg:mr-0 lg:ml-4 lg:order-2">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M12,3L1,9L12,15L21,10.09V17H23V9M5,13.18V17.18L12,21L19,17.18V13.18L12,17L5,13.18Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-blush-600 lg:order-1">2021</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">The Deep Dive</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  Determined to understand more, I enrolled in a <strong>Bachelor's in Information Technology</strong>. I learned data structures, algorithms, and core software design. Each concept felt like a puzzle waiting to be solved.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- 2022 - First Real Project -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
            <div class="lg:text-left">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-lavender-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-l-4 border-lavender-400">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-lavender-400 to-lavender-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M10,4H14V6H10V4M4,6H6V4A2,2 0 0,1 8,2H16A2,2 0 0,1 18,4V6H20A2,2 0 0,1 22,8V19A2,2 0 0,1 20,21H4A2,2 0 0,1 2,19V8A2,2 0 0,1 4,6M4,8V19H20V8H4Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-lavender-600">2022</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">First Real Project</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  At <strong>PPLWork</strong>, I worked on my first real-world project — a custom task manager. I designed backend APIs in Java, implemented RESTful microservices, and collaborated with real developers on shipping real features. It was thrilling to build something others could use.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- 2023 - ML & AI -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="lg:text-right">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-butter-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-r-4 border-butter-400">
                <div class="flex items-center lg:justify-end mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-butter-400 to-butter-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4 lg:mr-0 lg:ml-4 lg:order-2">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M12,2A2,2 0 0,1 14,4C14,4.74 13.6,5.39 13,5.73V7H14A7,7 0 0,1 21,14H22A1,1 0 0,1 23,15V18A1,1 0 0,1 22,19H21V20A2,2 0 0,1 19,22H5A2,2 0 0,1 3,20V19H2A1,1 0 0,1 1,18V15A1,1 0 0,1 2,14H3A7,7 0 0,1 10,7H11V5.73C10.4,5.39 10,4.74 10,4A2,2 0 0,1 12,2M7.5,13A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 5,15.5A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 7.5,18A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 10,15.5A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 7.5,13M16.5,13A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 14,15.5A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 16.5,18A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 19,15.5A2.5,2.5 0 0,0 16.5,13Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-butter-600 lg:order-1">2023</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">Machine Learning & AI</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  At <strong>TU Dublin</strong>, I dove into machine learning and AI. From neural networks to object detection, I was hooked. I realized the power of combining code with cognition — building systems that learn and adapt.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- 2024 - Current -->
          <div class="relative grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="hidden lg:block"></div>
            <div class="lg:text-left">
              <div class="inline-block p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 lg:border-l-4 border-sky-400">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                  <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-400 to-sky-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                      <path d="M12,2L13.09,8.26L22,9L13.09,9.74L12,16L10.91,9.74L2,9L10.91,8.26L12,2Z"/>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold text-sky-600">2024</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-3">The Journey Continues</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700">
                  Today, I'm working on an <strong>AI-enabled Online Examination Portal</strong> as my final year project. I'm exploring secure backend systems in Python, ML-based proctoring, and cloud-native architecture — while also polishing my frontend and DevOps skills.
                </p>
                <p class="text-sky-600 font-medium mt-3">
                  The best part? I'm still just as excited about coding as I was on day one.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Learnings -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-12 text-center">
        Key Learnings Along the Way
      </h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Code is Communication -->
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 to-mint-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-400 to-mint-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,2A10,10 0 0,0 2,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,22A10,10 0 0,0 22,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,2M17,7L12,17L7,7H17Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-4">Code is Communication</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700">
            Writing clean code isn't about cleverness — it's about clarity. Every function tells a story your future self will thank you for.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Embrace the Struggle -->
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-blush-50 to-lavender-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-blush-400 to-lavender-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,2C17.53,2 22,6.47 22,12C22,17.53 17.53,22 12,22C6.47,22 2,17.53 2,12C2,6.47 6.47,2 12,2M15.59,7L12,10.59L8.41,7L7,8.41L10.59,12L7,15.59L8.41,17L12,13.41L15.59,17L17,15.59L13.41,12L17,8.41L15.59,7Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-4">Embrace the Struggle</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700">
            Getting stuck is part of the process. Every bug is an opportunity to learn something deeper — persistence is the real superpower.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Community Matters -->
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-mint-50 to-butter-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-mint-400 to-butter-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M16,13C15.71,13 15.38,13 15.03,13.05C16.19,13.89 17,15 17,16.5V19H23V16.5C23,14.17 18.33,13 16,13M8,13C5.67,13 1,14.17 1,16.5V19H15V16.5C15,14.17 10.33,13 8,13M8,11A3,3 0 0,0 11,8A3,3 0 0,0 8,5A3,3 0 0,0 5,8A3,3 0 0,0 8,11M16,11A3,3 0 0,0 19,8A3,3 0 0,0 16,5A3,3 0 0,0 13,8A3,3 0 0,0 16,11Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-4">Community Matters</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700">
            The open-source world showed me that developers are generous learners. Teaching, sharing, and contributing feels like second nature.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Technology Serves People -->
        <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-lavender-50 to-sky-50 shadow-soft hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-lavender-400 to-sky-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,21.35L10.55,20.03C5.4,15.36 2,12.27 2,8.5C2,5.41 4.42,3 7.5,3C9.24,3 10.91,3.81 12,5.08C13.09,3.81 14.76,3 16.5,3C19.58,3 22,5.41 22,8.5C22,12.27 18.6,15.36 13.45,20.03L12,21.35Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-4">Technology Serves People</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700">
            The best software solves real problems. Whether it's an API or an AI model, I always ask: How does this make someone's life better?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-100 to-mint-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-800 mb-6">
        Next: The Tools That Power My Journey
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-700 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        You've seen where I've been — now let's look at the tools, stacks, and frameworks that help me bring my ideas to life.
      </p>
      <a href="/toolkit" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-500 to-mint-500 text-white font-medium hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105">
        <span>Read Chapter III: My Toolkit</span>
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</ChapterLayout> 